Detailed Description

Exposes methods to access Portable Executable (PE) Header fields.

Member Function Documentation

HRESULT INktStructPEFileHeader::Characteristics ( [out, retval] short *  pVal)
getoptional

Returns the image characteristics.

Parameters
pValPointer to receive the value. See official MSDN documentation http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms680313(v=vs.85).aspx for available constants.
HRESULT INktStructPEFileHeader::Machine ( [out, retval] short *  pVal)
get

Returns the machine architecture.

Parameters
pValPointer to receive the machine architecture, from the following values: IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_I386, IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_IA64 or IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64.
HRESULT INktStructPEFileHeader::NumberOfSections ( [out, retval] LONG *  pVal)
get

Returns the number of sections.

Parameters
pValPointer to receive the number of sections. This indicates the size of the section table, which immediately follows the headers. Note that the Windows loader limits the number of sections to 96.

get

HRESULT INktStructPEFileHeader::TimeDateStamp ( [out, retval] LONG *  pVal)
get

Returns the timestamp of the image.

Parameters
pValPointer to receive the value. This represents the date and time the image was created by the linker. The value is represented in the number of seconds elapsed since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970, Universal Coordinated Time, according to the system clock.
